:"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Run the PCR with the following cycler conditions<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/dgavbjtu7.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"275DB522E93D4483895F5C2ACBF65937","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/dgavbjtu7.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"ADD6E940A1FE11EBB79895B61C184829","order_id":3,"type_id":28,"title":"equipment","source":{"brand":"ABI","sku":"4351104","specifications":null,"can_edit":false,"name":"7500 Real Time PCR System","type":null,"link":null,"file":null,"image":null}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1173255,"guid":"4541085A677247518FF7A4FFC465CC09","previous_id":1173254,"previous_guid":"5D4A81D89A1A4828979485064A4E0D0E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7BCE81CF10D04C43AC51D67062120B45","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"893470F7AE8342E09F0EC9B0A3ECD35E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Data Evaluation<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"2B3D1BBC5A084A91B1271339101ED6D7","order_id":2,"type_id":17,"title":"result","source":{"body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/dgazbjtu7.jpg\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Results Interpretation:<\/div><table border><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\"><\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Size of the fragment<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Tm<\/td><\/tr><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">NSP6: \u0394S106; \u0394G107 e \u0394F108 <\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">60 bp<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\"><73,99\u00b0C<\/td><\/tr><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">NSP6: Wild type<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">69bp<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">\u226574\u00b0C<\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The emergence of SARS-CoV-2 variants with multiple shared mutations has been described to be more transmissible and could affect COVID-19 morbidity and mortality. Some of these variants, known as B.1.1.7 (originally described in the United Kingdom), B1.351 (originally described in South Africa), and P.1 (originally described in Brazil) have rapidly become dominant within their countries and require a vigorous public health response. Whole Genomic sequencing remains the gold standard method to identify the SARS-CoV-2 variant, even though this approach is laborious, time-consuming, and expensive. Here, we have developed a fast and simple SYBR green based real-time RT-PCR assay that identifies a distinct signature affecting the Non-Structural Protein 6 (NSP6), a nine-nucleotides deletion leading to amino acid losses: \u0394106S, \u0394107G, and \u0394108F. This NSP6 signature is present in the variants of concern (VOC) described above (B.1.1.7; B1.351; P.1) and has not been detected in other SARS-CoV-2 lineages.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1620231991}